				April 4, 2018 at 09:31					</a>
									</div><!-- .comment-meta .commentmetadata -->

				<div class="comment-body"><p>To become a member of the World Science Fiction Society, which includes the right to participate in the selection of the Hugo Awards, joint the current World Science Fiction Convention as at least a supporting member. Membership in the current Worldcon includes membership in WSFS. See the <a href="http://www.worldcon.org/" rel="nofollow">Worldcon web site</a> for links to the next two Worldcons, from whom you can buy your membership. You cannot purchase a membership directly from the WSFS or from TheHugoAwards.org. You must buy your membership from a Worldcon. The only way to join WSFS is to join the current Worldcon.</p>
</div>

